        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 2 at 3:04PM EDT until May 2 at 3:15PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 303 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 4 miles west of
Anderson, or near Anderson Airport, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind
damage to trees and power lines.

Locations impacted include...
Sadlers Creek State Park and Lake Hartwell.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
